<HEADLINE>
INTELLIGENT CITIES ICT FORUM OPENS IN TAIPEI
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, March 28 (CNA) 03/28/07  14:09:36 (By Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
The Taipei City government opened the 2007 Intelligent Cities ICT
Forum Wednesday, which it organized to promote cooperation among
major Asian cities in the field of information and communications
technology (ICT).
</P>
<P>
Representatives of members of the Asian Network of Major Cities
21 (ANMC21), including Tokyo, Jakata, Seoul and Kuala Lumpur; as
well as Intelligent Community Forum Chairman John Jung; Brenda
Halloran, mayor of Waterloo in Ontario, Canada; and
representatives of the local academic, governmental and
industrial sectors are attending the two-day forum being held at
the Howard International House for discussions aimed at working
out possible city collaboration models.
</P>
<P>
Forum topics include plans for national ICT development, the
Mobile Taiwan Program,  e-government,  Taipei's experiences  in
developing itself into "an Internet city, " and the leading role
a government should play in efforts to carry out ICT application
projects.
</P>
<P>
Taipei City has initiated ICT cooperation among Asian capital
cities at the forum with proposals categorized under four themes:
e-government, digital development imbalances, mobile applications
in public services, and knowledge management in public
departments.
</P>
<P>
Taipei Mayor Hau Lung-bin said the forum is serving as a platform
for "intelligent  cities" to conduct exchanges on ICT-relevant
knowledge and experiences in the implementation of ICT
applications, as well as to share ideas on future ICT
development.
</P>
